commit 7ffe3a213ccf102780f3704a67a821b7c188f12c
Author: Daniel Falbel <dfalbel@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 16 15:29:54 2026 -0300

    Generate C++ dispatchers for all remaining multi-overload functions

    For functions with 3+ overloads or complex dispatch patterns, generate a
    per-function C++ dispatcher that does type resolution and overload selection
    entirely in C++, calling each overload directly via Rcpp::as<>().

    This eliminates do.call, R-level cache lookups, and R↔C++ round-trips for
    the remaining ~12% of namespace and ~7% of method functions. torch_div
    (4 overloads) drops from 5.86µs to 2.34µs (-60%).

    No generated code uses call_c_function anymore — all dispatch is either
    direct, inline R if/else, or C++ dispatcher.
