Author: Daniel Falbel <dfalbel@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 16 18:31:44 2026 -0300

    Remove shared_ptr overhead from lantern type wrappers (#1441)

    * Remove shared_ptr overhead from lantern type wrappers

    Replace shared_ptr with direct value ownership in Box, ArrayBoxImpl,
    OptionalArrayRef, and self_contained string_view/DimnameList wrappers.

    These wrapper types are never shared — they're heap-allocated via
    make_ptr(), accessed through void*, and deleted via lantern_delete().
    The atomic reference counting in shared_ptr was pure overhead.

    Custom copy/move constructors ensure that internal ArrayRef/string_view
    members always point into the sibling buffer member after construction.

    * Retrigger CI
