commit 42c774348fb163aa5587c50b496c9e978ed53d95
Author: Daniel Falbel <dfalbel@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jan 28 12:28:35 2026 -0300

    Fix handling of R longjump exceptions in autograd and tracing callbacks (#1406)

    * Fix handling of R longjump exceptions in autograd callbacks

    Store the longjump token when catching LongjumpException in autograd
    callbacks and resume it properly in lantern_host_handler. This ensures
    R interrupts and other longjumps are handled correctly during backward
    passes instead of being converted to regular exceptions.

    - Add g_longjump_token global to store the token from LongjumpException
    - Modify LANTERN_CALLBACK_END to capture the longjump token
    - Update lantern_host_handler to resume longjump via R_ContinueUnwind
    - Add explicit lantern_host_handler() calls after backward operations
    - Add null checks for variable_list handling
    - Remove RCPP_NO_UNWIND_PROTECT flag to enable unwind protection

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

    * Add longjump exception handling to JIT tracing callbacks

    Extract maybe_resume_longjump() helper function and add longjump
    handling to trace.cpp for JIT tracing callbacks.

    - Add maybe_resume_longjump() helper in lantern.cpp
    - Refactor lantern_host_handler() to use the helper
    - Add LongjumpException handling in trace.cpp r_fn lambda
    - Call maybe_resume_longjump() in trace.cpp catch blocks

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

    ---------

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
